tweets.text: Please don’t be tempted to drive through floodwater. https://t.co/N0rfMwECd5

@amandarandall5 @EnvAgency We could never get understand all the building on flood plains round Bedford when we lived there, it was as if everyone had forgotten the 1998 floods. They have built on land that was under a couple of feet of water then.

@meandme3010 Glad she's safe! We spent Christmas eve shifting stuff upstairs just in case... Highest river levels since 2003 for us, quite amazingly coinciding with a huge amount of building on the floodplain. Strange huh? 
@EnvAgency #floodingalerts

tweets.text: Our team is out in #SouthHinksey #Oxford erecting a temporary flood barrier to protect properties from flooding. River levels have risen fast following heavy rainfall. Further rainfall is expected on Saturday and Sunday with #Storm Bella. Please stay #FloodAware. 1/2
Now my family in area of floods in Bedford. Daughter says it is worse than 1998. Luckily they live in an area that will not flood.

A massive thanks from me to all involved in this major incident @northantsfire @NorthantsEPTeam @NorthantsPolice @Northants_SAR @N44Response @Bucksfire @WarksFireRescue @EnvAgency also control room staff who took multiple calls. #interoperability https://t.co/TZvZbsIZID

Allermoor Spillway stopped running early this morning, we had personnel out opening Monksleaze Sluice to operate the SOWY at full capacity diverting excess flows from the Parrett as well as switching pumps on at some Langport stations ahead of storm Bella. @EnvAgencySW

150 m of temporary defence barrier up at #South Hinksey ,already protecting property ,a further 150 m to go . Great work by field teams #TeamEA ,⁦@EnvAgencySE⁩ ⁦@johncurtinEA⁩ ⁦⁦⁦@wifo_ea⁩ ⁦@SteveMooreEA⁩ ⁦⁦⁩ ⁦@MarkHill03⁩ https://t.co/hUrhJlFzYN
@norfolkbookworm @AnglianWater @EnvAgency @EnvAgencyAnglia @BroadsAuth Pictured 8pm Wednesday eve over the footbridge at the University campus. Have taken water samples too https://t.co/4GE3YvReRB

tweets.text:
We have issued two severe #flood warnings at Cogenhoe Mill Caravan Site and Billing Aquadrome due to flood risk in the #Northampton area.
 
We're working closely with the emergency services who are now evacuating these sites. Stay safe and don’t walk or drive through floodwater.

We currently have 12 flood warnings and 52 flood alerts in place for our area⚠️

Check your risk here: https://t.co/YIjsFwpg8o

Sign up to our flood alert service here: https://t.co/P6B5248RRV

#Flooding https://t.co/QEbV5oBUHE

Flood Alert declared by @EnvAgencySE  for River Thames from Hurley to Cookham. To report flooding in our area, or to contact the local Environment Agency Duty Officer, call the EA's Incident Hotline on 0845 850 3518. https://t.co/DwurrejLCc
The flood gate at #Uckinghall in Gloucestershire has just been closed by our ops team https://t.co/qJfmPiPXQW

A huge thank you to the @EnvAgencyMids team, one of which was out with me last night in the pouring rain checking on pumping equipment by the river and this morning the same person was out in waders digging out twigs, branches and a wheelie bin from the beck. #dedication 🎄👏🏻 https://t.co/5WqbqiTx4H

More rain is expected over the coming days 🌧️

Make sure you sign up to flood alerts from @EnvAgency ⚠️

#CambsFlooding https://t.co/QsDoWVNn8i

#Flooding doesn't know it's #Christmas so make sure you stay #FloodAware & follow our steps to #StaySafe
 
⚠️Check your #flood risk!

⚠️Sign up for free warnings!

⚠️Keep up to date with the latest situation: https://t.co/8HEpx25JxV https://t.co/G6OfXw4nHH
